The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close of trade in Lima.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell for a fifth session, dropping 1
percent to 20,224.52. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 1.1
percent to 2,692.48.  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc
and lead producer, dropped 7 percent to 40 centimos, a three-
year low, as the metals slumped in  London .  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the countryâ€™s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell 2.7 percent to $36.95 after
gold declined in  New York , said Carlos Arias, head of research
at Lima-based brokerage Andes Securities SAB.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, slid 2 percent to $1 as crude
fell in New York.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, dropped 1.6 percent to 62 centimos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
